\ In-place elementwise matrix arithmetic (+! -! *! /!): reuse the matrix
\ operand's buffer instead of allocating. A matrix operand is required.

\ matrix op scalar
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 10 +! .
[ 10 20 30 40 ] 2 2 matrix 5 -! .
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 3 *! .
[ 10 20 30 40 ] 2 2 matrix 10 /! .

\ scalar op matrix
10 [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix +! .
100 [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix -! .
4.0 [ 1 2 4 ] 1 3 matrix /! .

\ matrix op matrix (reuses the left operand)
[ 10 20 30 40 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix +! .
[ 10 20 30 40 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix -! .

\ shape mismatch
[ 1 2 ] 1 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 ] 1 3 matrix +!

\ requires a matrix operand
5 3 +!
